reviews.text: I went on a Saturday afternoon around 1 PM. I was seated right away. The place was pretty empty. There seemed to only be 2 servers in my area so it took a while for someone to come to me. When the server arrived, she was friendly and pleasant. I ordered the lobster, spinach, &  artichoke with cheese dip, and flounder sandwich with a salad where my 12 year old daughter got the Ultimate Feast that comes with a lobster tail, crab legs, two kinds of shrimp and 2 sides, along with a Shirley Temple drink. The dip was too salty for me. I didn't eat all of it. I wouldn't get it ever again. The salad was fine. I ate all of it. The fish sandwich came with Cole slaw. It was OK. My daughter even asked would I get that or a Fish Filet from McDonald's. I picked the latter. They have a lemon cake that I was tempted to get but declined. My server gave me a slice on the house right before I left. After tasting it, I'm so glad I didn't pay for it. The size is a little small and it's like they're trying to go for a key lime taste in a cake. It's just OK. I wouldn't get it again either. Maybe I need to just stick with salad and biscuits at Red Lobster. I never have any complaints with those two items.

We were served this dry piece of meat. We ordered a filet mignon that was supposed to be medium well and this is what we got. The server refused to return it to the kitchen. Truly embarrassing for a restaurant that is supposed to offer a “five-star” experience.

My experience here was okay. The lobster was very good, but there was very little meat on it. One thing that made the lobster very good was that it was wild-caught. The Caesar salad and the cheese biscuits were fairly good. The craft beer selection could be a lot better, there are very few to choose from.

Good things first. Biscuits are always good, and the chocolate cake with ice cream always awesome. Server friendly.

Why did I rate this a 1? The primary problem was the wait. We stayed for about an hour  and 20 min. Or so. This was incredibly frustrating! When you have two young kids, you know exactly what I mean. So that made things really tough. The wait to order... The wait to get appetizer....the wait to get lunch....the wait for the desert.... Wait for drinks....wait for the check.... I got the chicken tenders and they looked like they came strait from a frozen food bag. Light brown color and taste was so plain. No seasoning or taste. Big disapointment. No way I was going to send those back and wait another 15 min. Then the bathrooms. My wife said the women's bathroom....when walk in, your shoes make this noise because the floor is all sticky. The men's was not any better. It literally smelled like the monkey house at the zoo.  We won't go back. I really hope the management can read these comments and try to do better.
This is best lobster place in the world. I recommend all of them but shrimp pasta amazing one!
Best lunch spot, and the best wings I’ve ever had both lemon pepper and Buffalo. I would highly recommend. The customer service is so nice and the food even better. 10/10
The staff seems nice. Good wings. Large menu. Just started going there, so still trying to figure out what they cook REALLY good.
YES YES And more YES. Fast and friendly fresh pizza made to order they way you like it now. Go see HUGO he will set ya up

This place has gone done down hill. One of the cooks does Everything in a pair of gloves, and the service was dismissive and unaccommodating for there price. Won’t be returning and It was once decent.
Ordered delivery two weeks in a row. Went with wings and speciality pizzas both times. Everything was perfect both times. Fast delivery and kind service. Their website is easy to navigate as well.

name: Subway
vicinity: 275 South Van Dorn Street Space # 110, Alexandria

reviews.text: Staff was incapable of listening or preparing the sandwich correctly. They were told over 4 times what sandwich to make, and they still made the completely wrong sandwich. On top of that, the sandwich wasn't even made to the standards of the menu item - a disgusting sweet and tangy sauce was put on it. Threw the entire sandwich out. Never go to this Subway. Horrible experience. Incompetent employees, and you'll get ripped off. Avoid at all costs.
Online order pickup - Steak & Cheese - Where’s the meat?!? Pretty disappointing sandwich to say the least….

Ladies were rude had to explain 4+ times what i wanted because they were busy talking to eachother not even about work also overcharged me for extra sauce and also they need to learn how to talk to people they were rude by talking about other people sitting in the restaurant
Man, those ladies in the restaurant simply do not care lol they were missing half of the toppings, the lettuce was drier than I don't know what, they were low-key rude. Wouldn't come back here tbh
Friendly and professional staff, clean facilities

Okay so before I go on this rant - I lead a team whose jobs are customer centric. Making sure we keep the customer first and provide an amazing customer experience so with all that being said I understand no one is perfect.

My issue with this establishment is that I was literally racially profiled. I walk in smiling like I always do when I enter any business and spoke to man at the register.  Not only did he look at me not speak and walk away the two gentlemen cutting the pizzas also looked at me and continued their conversation. Then a young man who’s race I will not assume but he was definitely not black walks and he receives a greeting from the very gentlemen who initially ignored me.  I then continue to make uncomfortable eye to eye contact with the gentleman who initially ignored me - when the young black man who was making the pizza finally offers me assistance.  This was  was embarrassing and hurtful. There is no way a business owner should allow this kind of bigotry in an establishment they own. I will be reaching out to corporate to report this. A completely demoralizing and hurtful experience.

I ordered 2 pizza when they had their 50% off deal and the total was $26 now tell me why I check my bank account and see that they charged me $34??? They robbed me out of $8 which I know it’s nothing but why would they overcharge me without my knowledge and permission? I’m gonna contact my bank right now and dispute the transaction cause this is a scam. Also the pizza was pretty bad and now understand why it was discounted at 50% off literally one of the worst ones I’ve ever had and it’s unexpected from dominos. Do not eat here if you want some mid pizza and get scammed for it too!

I ordered food yesterday (November 16) & waited over a hour for my food to be delivered.I called several times & no one one answered. Finally when I got someone they said they couldn’t find my order with my number! They didn’t seem to care to help me at all. So I ended up having to drive there while I’m sick just to figure out what’s going on with my food. I got there & they said they thought I canceled! MIND you I called so how could I have cancelled if I never called to cancel!? As I was there I had to wait additional 30 mins just for fresh food! While I was there I even got hit on by a employee how inappropriate & professional.

Great pizza - always consistently good. We order from this dominos all the time - and every experience we’ve had has been great. Since I can’t eat dairy, I always say no cheese please, and they have always gotten my order right. Never been for pick up, so can’t comment there! Always very affordable with a pizza tracker to estimate how long it will take!

This location has some of the worst customer service and pizza I've ever encountered. There have been several times I have never received my order after it was claimed to have been delivered through their app and their updating service. When I try to call for a refund no one ever picks up the phone and the few times I can talk to someone on the phone they are incredibly unhelpful and I have had to resort to a chargeback on my credit card to get a refund. Order pizza from anywhere else but here.

name: Thai Lemon Grass
vicinity: 506 South Van Dorn Street C, Alexandria

reviews.text:
I ordered a small Tom Yum. It was tasty , the chicken was a bit dry and chewy but maybe that was because I placed an order 20 minutes before closing.

It was a to go order , I just poured the soup in a nice bowl to take a nice photo.
Their food is delicious, their Thai curry is my favorite! I️ also appreciate being able to pick how hot I️ like it. I️’ve been here multiple times and have never been disappointed.
Ordered the Tom yum chicken. Medium spice. It was water with chicken and no flavour. The beef salad was bland as well. I’m from south Florida and have never had such awful food.

I ordered the Tom Yum and Pad Thai with a Thai beer and let me tell you everything tasted authentic! I went all out and ordered the full scoop to give you an good review and I am so glad I did so. I really enjoyed the Tom Yum soup because the broth was just right and so was the level of spice. As for the Pad Thai, it was also great because it had the right amount of peanut sauce taste in it. The beer was amazing and had a fresh light taste. If you are in the NOVA area and looking for some authentic tasting Thai food, I would highly recommend stopping by here to give it a try.

Not sure I’ll recommend this place to anyone. The lady seems nice but the food was terrible. No flavor whatsoever. This is my first time ever writing a food review. I usually let it slide but this was bad I had to say something. I spent $50 and I had to give the food away to someone else. The assorted fried rice was the worst.

I ordered a Dave's Single, this was $5.99. Look at the hamburger they gave me. Do you see any beef? I drove 20 minutes back home to find this in my bag. How do you not put the beef in a hamburger? What were you thinking, who's working back there? I called and asked for the Manager. They told me the manager is not in today. I will certainly call tomorrow. Please avoid this Wendy's. This is not the first time I had Customer Service issues here, and this was the last time I am visiting this place.
I ordered 2 kids meals for my kids, and the food was hot and fresh when I picked up. However, the disappointment was the store’s restroom need to improve soon.

This Wendy never disappoints. Me and my family mainly always come to this Wendy because they have great service and I never have to wait to long for my food. The food is always warm and it is salted properly. I’ve been to some Wendy’s and the fries would be cold even though no one was there. So I appreciate there hard work on making the fries and everything warm.

let’s start off by when I was ordering I asked for extra sauce..wasn’t in the bag when I received it then I ask again politely and she gives me an attitude tells me I have to pay which I obviously didn’t mind doing I leave I get home and as soon as I open my sandwhich I find a black piece of hair like bro that’s disgusting just wasted money for what like I’m prob never going to wendys again and if I do it def won’t be this one

Wendy's is always a solid spot to grab a quick meal. There food has actually gotten better with the addition of the baconator. But I didn't grab the baconator on this visit. I ordered the Bourbon Bacon burger and it was so delicious. We also got the spicy chicken nuggets. YOU CANNOT GO TO WENDYS AND NOT ORDER THE SPICY CHICKEN NUGGETS! Overall delicious experience.

This Starbucks is very close to the Van Dorn metro station. I decided to give it a try in spite of the bad comments.
It’s a small/medium space. I liked they had plants in one corner, it made it feel cozy. The baristas were helpful when my order was delivered incorrectly and seemed pretty friendly in general. Unfortunately, the comments about the lack of cleanliness are true: the coffee shop and the restroom were not clean at all. It’s unfortunate since the place’s got great potential.
Also, bare in mind the parking situation: You’ll need to download the “Pango” app and there’s limited parking spots (20min, 2hr). I’ve attached an image for reference.
Hopefully, they take serious actions towards the cleanliness. It would really elevate the experience for customers.

A Starbucks desperately in need of better management. I was in the neighborhood for business and stopped here for an hour. Warm and prompt services. However this store is a mess in terms of cleanliness. Early in the morning when it just opened not for long, trash everywhere, not to mention there’s a huge cockroach crawling slowly right in the middle of the first restroom on the right hand side. I highly doubt that the store had any proper cleaning before the opening today and after closing last night.

This store was my favorite store to get my coffee every day for years, unfortunately now there services disappointed me with there bossy customer services and disrespectful. this morning when I ordered my coffee they show at the apps it will be ready in 12 minutes but unfortunately when I get to store it took me 49 minutes and there were working 5 people and was slow not to much customer , after that long time waiting I checked for 3 time with store manager and other employees to make sure that they are making my coffee or not they were so bossy and finally they give a wrong coffe 🤯🤯🤯🤯🤯🤯 I have to stop  getting coffee from this careless and bossy stuffs at this store 🤯🤯🤯🤯🤯🤯🤯🤯

I enjoued being at this starbucks, the staff are friendly and the place is clean. there is a table of condiments if you need any. the service was a bit slow because the place was crowded but I ordered on the app and got a fadt service.

Staff friendly, book exchange contributes to a warm vibe, barista made my drink perfectly (some places go too extra on almond milk). Parking probably could be a bit of a challenge. Space is the most concealed Starbucks I've ever seen but it's actually cozy and not cold and sterile feeling
Great spot for Ethiopian food. Beautiful interior and great service. The food selection was impressive. I had the vegetable platter which is way enough for 2:meals. Everything was very good.

Very disappointed! This is the first restaurant that doesn’t answer their phone. I ordered through Uber eats with multiple ordered. I found hair inside the Quanta Firfir. Very disappointed and almost threw up. So I dumped everything in the trash. I didn’t expect such thing for a fancy looking Ethiopian restaurant.
The place is very nice. Friendly staff and servers. The food is great. Love the place.
Live Ethiopian music Friday Saturday and Sunday. Very clean and sophisticated place with people dressed smart. The food is very delicious and the service is great as well.
Delicious Ethiopian food. Best one I’ve had in the area. Great music. Friendly service. The portions were also perfect to share.

I ordered 2 spicy chicken sandwiches and large fries from the app.🍟

I picked up in-store, however I glad had Mario’s help and friendly service to organize the front lines. Save ourselves time grab and go. 👍

I was actually walking today, and I had some business to do at a nearby bank.  I came here because I knew that I had a coupon for a free quarter pounder with cheese sandwich when you buy one.  St $6.00 for the sandwich, you can't knock me for trying to save money.  The once change that I didn't like about this location, as well as, several others is the fact that they have moved the self serve fountain drink machine to behind the counter. In years past you could refill all day long- joking of course!  The point is I can see how many fast food places like this are cutting corners in order to save money.  The quarter pounder with cheese is good, and I will save the second one for later.

I ordered a hot fudge sundae and got it right away, so I can't complain about the service.  There was trash left on the tables and floor, so I don't think surfaces are cleaned or floors mopped as often as they should be.

food was what you come to expect from them however service is garbage zero respect for customers or their jobs the whole place was dirty every table floors bathroom all gross and I know what your thinking probably just had a rush lol nope been there 3 times now and won't be going back. I guess the days of being proud to work are gone for these folks, and now we get to pay triple to have these garbage employees treat us with no respect or even be polite at least a couple of other chain restaurants pride themselves as friendly and polite and happy to have your business well I'm pretty much done with the clown and his employees good luck you've been warned

Every single time I order from this places it either misses items or it completely messes the whole order up. I'm not bringing my business back here ever again. I'd rather go to any other McDonald's than this one. Employees are rude and not willing to try and give me any kid of credit or anything for their mistake. I don't like driving all the way out there but every time I order on doordash they mess it up too. Every single time.

Good spot ! Service was great . I got the chicken and waffles that was okay I like when it’s actual chicken legs, thighs , or wings instead of a chicken fillet style but it was still good . The Mac and cheese I wasn’t a fan of so I barley ate that . The wings for an appetizer was a good start fresh and hot which was great ! The bayou shrimp sandwich was good but the bun was actually a little hard maybe just needed to be warmed up. Will I be going back yea eventually but maybe not anytime soon. I do recommend giving this spot a try 👍🏼

Stopped here one evening looking for a place to eat and being out of town, we thought we’d give this a shot. It was definitely way better than I anticipated it to be! The pizza and burger were amazing, and the staff was extremely friendly. If we’re ever back in the area, I’d love to stop again.

We went here for brunch and ordered the breakfast pizza and New Orleans breakfast bowl. It didn’t disappoint. Amber was our waitress and our food came out really fast. There was no wait to be seated and we were sad we couldn’t try out the cocktails due to our schedules for the day but we will definitely be back. Amber was knowledgeable and attentive to our questions about the menu. I wish there were more vegetarian and vegan options however.

My family recommended this place. And it was disappointing. Right off the bat. The staff was not welcoming at all. Our waitress was ice cold. My wife's Ceasar Salad and Clam Chowder was the worst she has ever had. But, my Philly Cheesesteak was legit good. It is up there with Gino's and Pat's in Philly.

Harvey was super great! Very attentive and helpful, and the food was fresh and delicious. There wasn’t a long wait to eat, and the ambiance in the restaurant is very cozy. You will definitely enjoy this place! A must visit if you are in the Alexandria area.

Just what I wanted for lunch today.  The chicken sandwich and fries was only $9.99 for a moist and flavorful sandwich loaded with rotisserie chicken with thick fries on the side.  I tried the fruity Maranon drink this time.  The restaurant got crowded, but tables are spaced apart, so I felt comfortable.  Lots of windows for the sunshine to make the dining area bright and warm.  The music made it just perfect for a satisfying, relaxed lunch.
Friendly staff and good food! No disappointment here. I do recommend a visit. Clean dining room. Outside is a little rough but ok.
Valeria helped me order the beef fried rice special and it was so delicious.  Everyone is so friendly and the music isn't too loud, just the right volume of Latin music. I will definitely be back.

I have used Inca Chicken twice as a caterer for my dinner parties in the DMV and people love the food especially the rotisserie chicken! Edwin, the owner, is a great partner to develop the menu needed for the party. They give great customer service and did I say the food is delicious! #Alexandria #Arlington #DC #Maryland

First order out after our move and with so many Peruvian chicken places around we have this a shot. My wife ordered the lomo saltado and I did 1/2 chicken with yucca fries and rice & beans.

The lomo saltado was good. Saucy, a bit of flavor from maybe fresh cilantro, decent beef, and I think the white rice was seasoned slightly (might have just been salt, but like the right amount.) The chicken had a nice, subtle smokiness to it. Now I know for delivery you're not going to keep a crispy skin, but it was hot from the grill. Yucca fries were a good size. Yucca isn't that flavorful, but they were great dipped in the green sauce (a little spicy). Rice & beans were fine.

A solid meal and now I think it's a good bar to compare other local chicken places with.

name: Pho Viet Flare Restaurant
vicinity: 4612, 514 South Van Dorn Street B, Alexandria

reviews.text:
I've been going to this place for over 15 years.  It's my favorite Vietnamese Pho restaurants in Northern VA. The food has never disappointed.  My kids love the food and the bubble tea.

If I could take a half star instead of full star I would.  The half star is because the prices have gone up ridiculously for lunch.

I’ve been to so many Vietnamese restaurants and honestly 5 starts isn’t enough for this place. Place is clean and nice, customer service is amazing from the hostess and waitresses to food being so delicious. I drive 25-30min from MD just to eat at this place. Welcoming and also with very fair prices. I just love this place.

This place rocks! They are super nice and the food is so good. My go to's are the fresh summer rolls and the pho, of course.  I was happy to see they now have shrimp pho. I always get take away and everything is always packaged so well and the portions are generous. I get 2-3 servings from one large pho!
the pho wasn’t too bad but it wasn’t that good either for me to come back. the soup didn’t have much flavor and the noodles were kind of hard. fast service though and very nice staff :)
rocket shrimp and shrimp cake vermicelli was delicious! just wish the nuoc mam was stronger tasting - more sweet than salty.

I ordered various breakfast items and when I bit into one of the breakfast burritos it tasted like chemicals. When i check the other side of the burrito it was covered in particles of powdered bleach. Every food item had powdered bleach on the tortilla. The manager was non apologetic and did not see this as a big deal. Also to mention when I went inside the cleaning/maintenance employee was standing on top of the food prep table next to the grills.

Staff was not professional or helpful. I placed an order through tcobell website, order tracker showed it is ready. Drove to the store, waited like 5 minutes with no one on the counter, finally a staff member showed up but was about to walk away again quickly. I asked her about my order, she said they are working on it. I told her the website says it's ready 20 minutes ago. She started to get angry asking for the name on the order again and 3 minutes later they told me the order is not in their system, it was never made. I said to myself okay that could happen sometimes, so I asked for preparing the order and get what i paid for, then my second shock was when the  response from the store manager that they will not do that, they will not prepare any order or even refund me and I need to call customer service. I showed her the online order, the receipt email and the order status showing ready for pick up from her store , without any luck. I had to reorder again in the store my, pay again and only to find that the order was wrong when I arrived home. At that point I gave up. Don't go there!

I do not know what changed recently but the service is much much slower now than it was a few months ago. The drive through is extremely slow. I loved coming here before because of how fast you guys were. The quality/amounts used to be better too. You guys are being a little stingy now.

11/7/22. Food made incorrectly. Wait times too long!!  Horrible management!! Placed my mobile order at 7:08pm.   Mobile app said it was ready for pick up around 7:15pm. Walked in with no one in sight to attend to me along with one other customer already waiting for their order.  Another customer comes in after me and is also waiting.  No line in drive-thru.   As I'm waiting in the front area, I see through the kitchen door window, someone sitting on a stool laughing. After waiting until 7:30pm, the customer who came in after me yells "HELLOOO??!!" Finally, someone comes out to help us.  It was the same lady who was laughing in the back doing nothing. She helps the customer and then helps me.  After waiting about 20-25 min, I get my order of 6 tacos!!! I drive home and find my order is all wrong and I can't eat it.  I had to go drive back.

I speak to the manager, Simon and request my order be remade.  Had to teach Simon step by step how to order on the app.  I also tell him it's your responsibility to attend to the customers in the store.  He responds we do have people in the front. I then told him the other customer who came in after me had to yell out "HELLO!!"  I then told him anyone can come in here and steal anything.  I also asked why is the food out in the pickup area.  He stated they no longer put it in the pick up area because food is being stolen.   Well, it's probably being stolen because no one is watching the front.

This isn't the first time I've ordered the same food here.  In the end, I wasted one hour to get 6 tacos!!   That's two round-trips!!  What a waste of my time!!   Why is this Taco bell service so slow even when there's no line in the drive thru?  It's clear,  Simon does not know how to manage this store. This place desperately needs new management.  Simon has to go.

Also, look at this.  Does this Mexican pizza look like the pizza they show in their app?  I don't think so.  The quality and service here just sucks.  Fire the management!!

Not much to say... this is a pretty small TB. We've recently tried going in because our order would regularly be missing items or just be wrong. I found a lot of guys go in there only to use the bathroom 🙃. Nope... you very much get what you pay for.

Great value for price. Supper fast delivery. After trying resturant first time through UberEats. I stopped by one time for Pickup realized they have their own delivery. Make sure you Support resturant by ordering directly from them, only $1 delivery fee, I always get my food within 20 min of ordering. Driver in silver Toyota always sharp & polite. (Still puts on new gloves & wears mask for every delivery) always working hard.
My favorite-Chow Foon
Rice Noodles Taiwan or Singapore Style- also great spring & eggroll for only $1.5 each
Pad Thai could be better, least favorite is curry chicken. Would love to see a Thai curry on menu maybe a Phanaeng curry.
Overall not the best Chinese resturant out there but deserves 5 stars, big portions, good, clean food, always consistent hot & fresh and a five star delivery service that will never miss all for a great price. Value %100

The food is AWFUL 🤮.  I've lived in this area for 25 years.  This place changed ownership and it has been the worst ever since.  None of the food ever tastes good.  It's never a hit-or-miss. It's always a miss.  They can't even do wonton soup or fry an egg roll.  I used to eat here all the time and I can honestly say that I will never ever ever ever ever ever ever ever ever ever ever ever ever eat at this place again in my life.  NOTHING is good at this place.

My wife and I used to absolutely love this place. We lived at the apartments right behind it and would order take out at least one a week. I'm not sure what has happened there in the last few months but the quality has dropped all around. Not only is the food not as good as it used to be, but today my wife ordered a Chicken fried rice and received a shrimp fried rice instead even after having a conversation with the individual taking the order about whether the egg rolls have shrimp since she hates shrimp and all of the places around here have switched to using it for some reason and this is like the third time in a row something has been wrong with the order. I'm leaving two stars because it is still a good deal, but I hope they get their act together by the time we are willing to try again in a couple of months...

I’m putting one star because I can’t put less but the food here is horrible I ordered the orange chicken that comes with a rice,soup, and a spring roll the rice is mushy and bland and the orange chicken tastes burnt and has no flavoring at all they didn’t even but in the soup and when we called back all they said was “ we can’t do anything about it that’s what you ordered” DO NOT EAT FROM HERE.

Found a piece of metal wiring in my food, luckily I spotted it before eating it. I don't know how a hard piece of metal gets in rice but it was large and seriously could've done damage. I was a loyal patron until yesterday smh

I got a smoothie, some egg rolls and a chicken and rice platter. Only the smoothie and the egg rolls were good. The chicken tasted just not good. Boyfriend got fried rice and he liked it for the most part. Smoothies are 10/10

The pho is pretty good, soup and meat is yummy. The veggies were not fresh, some brown spots were spotted on the basil and the jalapeño looks like they were defrosted.
The Thai tea and peach tea were great!

Decent place- probably won’t be back though. The mushrooms in my Pho frankly tasted dirty. The broth and everything else was good though. I also ordered soft spring rolls and unfortunately they were completely torn apart by the time I got home *pictured*. Most of the veggies spilled out which almost made them inedible. I placed my order online and the man at the front was rude, but the lady who was cooking in the back who brought my food out to me was very nice!

Absolutely love this place! It is the best every single time. The broth is beautiful on its own and the noodles are perfectly cooked. I love the tendon and tripe when I come. The young man who waiters there is so sweet and attentive. The crispy egg rolls are so good that we each have to get our own order, and sometimes seconds. It definitely can get busy but they do a great job of making sure you are satisfied. DEFINITELY RECOMMED TO ANYONE :)

So good!! Menu has a range of pho, noodle, and rice dishes. We got Pho Ga (small and large). You can add fresh bean sprouts, basil, lime, jalapeño peppers, chili oil, Sriracha, or soy sauce. Fast service and good prices too. We dined in. It looks recently renovated and is clean.👍

My husband and I had dinner 3/4/2022, made reservations for 6pm. Once sat, it took a while for our table to be greeted; we were not told of the days special(s). I noticed the table(s) sat after us were greeted more promptly told the day(s) special given bread/water upon being sat. Our waitress was very inattentive and slow seemed to pay attention to her other tables versus ours. We continuously had to ask for everything, i.e., refills, bread, and our check twice. (Not a good feeling) Especially when dinner for two was close to $100.
The food, however, was good; we enjoyed Cardon Bleu, mozzarella fritta, clams casino.
I am giving 4 stars because of food quality. 1-star customer service.
Hopefully, during our next visit, we have a more attentive waitress/waiter who treats all customers the same.

Restaurant is recommended 👌

Friendly service and amazing food. The price was higher than expected, they brought us the wrong appetizer, and our entrees took a little longer than they should have, but it was still a great experience. Bottom line - the food was excellent. Significantly better Italian fare than I've had anywhere else.

I made reservations here for my wife birthday dinner and the historic decor was beautiful and also the food was very much worth every penny and more, the service was great as well.
I wanted my wife to have her favorite food “Italian” in a nice classy restaurant and she had no leftovers (literally ate every crumb and some of my food too) lol and she was smiling the entire time.
We will definitely be back soon!!!

We had my moms 82nd surprise birthday party at Fratelli’s in Alexandria on Sunday, September 26.  We were able to bring in our decorations. Everything was beautiful and mom was surprised.  I love the ambiience and aromas that come from this place!

We had appetizers, calamari and fried mozzarella. The bread and salad were amazing.  That could have been my meal!  The main course was Linguini Cacciatore, Shrimp Alfredo, Pollo Alla Francese and grilled chicken.  Everything we ate was fresh and delicious. Manuel chef/owner uses the best quality ingredients to produce dishes that are authentic.

The service was of the highest quality.  Manuel was accommodating in every way.  Warm and very thoughtful.  He came around to check on our experience and seemed to be authentically engaged.  The waiters were very friendly, available, attentive and quick to take care of our needs.

I'm looking forward to the next party!

Thank you Manuel and staff for a wonderful celebration!!

Authentic Italian restaurant with friendly service,  very reasonable prices, and carefully prepared dishes! I ordered the spaghetti and meatballs, which I believe had a balanced flavor and texture. The atmosphere of the restaurant makes an ideal date night location, and the cannoli had the right amount of sweetness. Grazie!!

name: The Club Burger and Hot Chicken

reviews.text:
Best Chicken Tenders I’ve ever hands down! Went with Chicken and Waffles with Mild tenders and they were perfectly breaded and the flavor rub is 🤩. They were juicy and delicious! The wings were amazing, as well! The sando sandwich with the slaw was winner winner chicken - you know what I mean!!

A place can have great food, but if the service is bad then I won’t go back..not here!! Great customer service. Even my 10 y/o noticed, “it’s so nice he came and asked us how our food is”. This is an order-at-counter spot, so you don’t see that often.  Will be going back and recommending to all!!

On our hunt for the DMV’s best fried chicken sandwich we came across a hidden gem in Alexandria. If I’m not mistaken, the fried chicken sandwich is new to here menu. I was impressed to say the least. The flavor, texture, AND SIZE of this sandwich was/is definitely unmatched. This sandwich made a jump on our top 28 list to number 3. No regrets. If you are around the area, you should make an effort to go. The price was reasonable as well.

Great place to visit for deliciousness. The Sando Chicken Sandwich comes in a few spice options. I selected mild which for me was a decent amount of heat. The breading was light but not overpowering with seasoning. Chicken breast was BIG and juicy which didn’t disappoint. Fries are double cooked with no grease and doesn’t leave you feeling heavy. If you haven’t made your way here yet….what are you waiting for!!!

SO GOOD. had the veggie burger and it was one of the best I’ve had in this area! My husband had “the original” chicken sando and loved it. Fries were delicious too! Everyone was so kind also :) will definitely be coming back!

Been here twice now and got the chicken sandwich.  First of all, it's worth the 8-10 minutes wait.  Nice and crispy, and most importantly dat crunch survived the car trip home both times.  The filet itself is big, and it's juicy and tender and the whole thing is well seasoned all the way through.

Medium heat was not very spicy, but hot was perfect for me.  A pretty big step up which made me sweat just the right amount.  Will definitely visit again when I've got a chicken sandwich craving.

This place is every underrated. The food tasted amazing, especially the lomo saltado, it was so delicious. The horchata was also so flavorful and tasted amazing, I’ll excited to come back for more. They also have a sign outside that says they have karaoke nights, and inside they have some gambling machines and hookahs, so seems like a fun place to come to at night as well.

Where do i begin. Food is terrible. Everything is served in paper plates, coffee is in a styrofoam cup, sugar is in food prep bottle, and the whole place looks like my aunties living room. Literally, anyways i digress. Customer service was okay up until the DJ said in spanish, You animals don’t like my Christmas music ?! At his DJ stand beyond drunk… because he had been drinking at the bar the whole time we were there. Both the food and staff terrible, but i think if i had to choose which was the worst. It was the food. Lastly, they are charging 11% tax on your food, charging 15% tip on the total amount after tax, and their receipt? No itemization. When i asked for an explanation on the 11% she said thats the tax they charge everyone, its standard.

My coworker was sick on Monday, so I order a chicken soup from this place.(first Hispanic place I found) I was charged $18.81 for a chicken soup, lady on the phone said I could only pay with CC before picking up.. I said fine, I didn't ask how much the soups were because I was looking at their menu online and it says $8.95, I went to pick up and I get no receipt and I noticed on my account it was $18.81 for the soup. I called the lady (she was the only one at the restaurant) to ask for their chicken soup price, at first she said are you picking it up or dining in? I said pick up and she said $18, I said isn't that the seafood soup? (which its $16.45 or something on their menu) she said no, the seafood soup is $19.. $1 more than a chicken soup? seafood soups I know they are expensive but chicken soup? anyways I told her if they had changed their menu recently and this is what she said " UYYYY hace 10 a?os" meaning 10 years ago..  and she hang up on me. My mistake was to not ask for the total before paying but she kept insisting I need to pay I need to pay and if I was sure I was picking up and If I lived closed. I think is not the first time she overcharged someone and added to her Tip account or whatever, but not even on Grubhud their soup is almost $19, is $15.45 which it may be because is a delivery fee or whatever.
Honestly paying the $18.81 was not an issue if that was the real price for it, but her intention & attitude was just horrible!! Imagine how many people she has ripoff.
Anyways just be careful when ordering over the phone.
I went by chance and my order was very taste, and fresh but they need to work with more professional waiters
If possible 0.  Turned away their only customer to upcharge them because no business.  Horrible experience.  Do not go.
I did return today and not happy about this order. The steak was way overcooked and  the fries were old and refried. You can do better!!!!

I ordered online and got a XL pizza and mild boneless wings. My food came hot, fresh, and good. My food came before time whic I was pleased about and I enjoyed everything I haven’t had a good pizza like this in awhile. Happy Customer

Good place for a quick bite. I was disappointed that you can only order by the slice at lunchtime, and dinner requires you to buy a whole pizza. But it wasn't super expensive (definitely not cheap though) and food was fast enough that I didn't notice the wait. Plain cheese pizza, sue me, and garlic knots plus a drink put me right at $15. Dining area is a bit small but their main thing seems to be delivery anyway. Recently remodeled so it looks pretty nice and clean.

I just had a really negative experience. The driver wasn’t satisfied with my tip and expressed his feelings towards me about it. I do not feel this is appropriate and will no longer be utilizing this location. I called the store and they acted like they were going to talk to the manager about it but we all know how that goes. I feel he did this because I’m a person of color. Regardless of his reasoning tips are not mandatory in other countries only in the US. I tipped accordingly. Pay a living wage so the workers don’t have to depend on tips to supplement their income. I could see if I left no tip. This was completely uncalled for and inexcusable. The store didn’t offer a refund or anything.

I usually get the 2 slices of pizza and soft drink deal when I'm at Van Dorn Plaza and want a quick lunch.  It's around $7, including tax.  Other customers seemed to be enjoying their subs and there are lots of other items on the menu.  It's a tiny place, so best to come early if you want to sit at a table.

The food is extremely tasty and they have a wide variety of plates. This time I ordered an Argentinian style Milanesa Napolitana, after having tried this dish in other upscale restaurants I have to say this is the best one so far. Also saltenhas are great. Highly recommended.
I go to different Bolivian eateries in the DMV. The food that I ordered was great! Silpancho, Lomo Chorellana y Salteñas. With mocochinche to drink.  Well done guys!

I like this place for their food and bakery. On weekends they make one of the best peanut soups in the area. Definitely try their Milanesa neapolitana and steaks. About cakes,
They look super delicious but mostly very dry. Other point is their pastry. It is so fresh and yummy. Very good spot for Latin American food
Only Saltañias are good. But they don't know what the time is. They told me my order would be ready in 20 to 30 min. I was waiting there for more than 1 hour and 15 minutes.
The salteñas were mouthwatering!  The Tranca Pecho was excellent
